Organizers are registering more and more reservations.
A good winter is promising for German tour operators.
According to one study, the traffic of road reservations for the following months increased significantly compared to the previous year – by more than 30 percent for the winter season.
Despite the weak economic outlook, the Germans’ travel mood did not decline, according to the study.
Travel agencies recorded a 31 percent increase in sales for the winter season compared to the previous year, the German Travel Association (DRV) announced on Monday in Berlin.
According to the GfK market research institute, the number of bookings in the autumn months is already higher.
The turnover of travel agencies in October was 11 percent higher than in October 2007, DRV reported.
These results are based on data from GfK, which evaluates monthly booking data from 1,200 German travel agencies and then extrapolates it to the entire market.
The Institute took into account travel booked until the end of August 2008.
Due to the weak dollar exchange rate, travel to the US is particularly sought after, the DRV said.
Here, the number of reservations increased by about one-third.
Germans are also particularly fond of Spain, Turkey and Greece, as well as the domestic landscapes.
